nepali-calendar (1.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Swipe gesture switched to GestureDrag with CAPTURE propagation phase.
  * Week view cards redesigned: weekday name inside each card at top.
  * Today card gets accent-tinted background; Saturday card uses red text.

 -- Dhiraj Shah <me.dhirajshah@gmail.com>  Sun, 04 May 2026 00:00:00 +0545

nepali-calendar (1.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * BS/AD toggle button label now updates correctly.
  * Today circle perfectly centered using Gtk.Overlay fixed-size box.
  * EN/NP language toggle added; all labels and numbers switch languages.
  * Week view, Month view, Year view with Adw.ViewSwitcher tab bar.
  * Swipe left/right gesture for month and week navigation.
  * Full Nepali weekday names in Devanagari script.
  * Font sizes increased; AD mode header shows correct AD month/year.
  * Language preference persisted in settings.json.

 -- Dhiraj Shah <me.dhirajshah@gmail.com>  Sun, 04 May 2026 00:00:00 +0545

nepali-calendar (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial release.
  * GTK4 + libadwaita native desktop calendar.
  * Nepali Bikram Sambat (BS) primary view with AD secondary dates.
  * Public holiday highlighting for BS 2080-2086.
  * BS/AD mode toggle, today accent, light/dark mode support.
  * Window state persistence via ~/.config/nepali-calendar/settings.json.
  * nepali-datetime 1.0.8 bundled as vendor dependency.

 -- Dhiraj Shah <me.dhirajshah@gmail.com>  Sun, 04 May 2026 00:00:00 +0545
